comments: Carroll (BKN) gains possession of the ball and is awarded a timeout prior to any possible held ball.
Allen (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Gilgeous-Alexander (LAC) and makes marginal contact with his arms.
Williams (LAC) places a resting forearm to the side of Allen (BKN) and does not apply any force to affect his play at the basket.
[Observable in enhanced video] Williams (LAC) slides his pivot foot.
Harrell (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Harris (BKN) makes incidental contact to the body of Williams (LAC) after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Allen (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Allen (BKN) and Harrell (LAC) engage and disengage on the rebound.
RLS shows Harrell (LAC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Allen (BKN) during the play at the basket.  Any contact to the arm after the ball is dislodged should be considered incidental.
RLB shows Russell (BKN) briefly grasps the arm of Williams (LAC) off ball but does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
Harrell (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Harris (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Allen (BKN) makes contact to Williams' (LAC) body during his shooting motion that affects his jump shot attempt.
LLB shows Allen (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position from a wide stance and makes leg to leg contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (LAC) on the pick.
Gilgeous-Alexander (LAC) places a hand/arm to the front of Dinwiddie (BKN) on the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Carroll (BKN) commits a take foul on Harrell (LAC).
[Observable in enhanced video] Multiple players enter the lane prior to the release of the free throw.

Williams (LAC) and Carroll (BKN) engage and separate during the rebound and the ball goes out of bounds.  After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of Clippers possession is overturned to Nets possession.
Allen (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Beverley (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Beverley (LAC) briefly grasps the leg of Allen (BKN) when he engages on the pick but the contact does not affect his FOM.
MOB shows Carroll (BKN) grabs Gilgeous-Alexander's (LAC) arm and the contact affects his FOM during the inbound.
MOB and RAR show Carroll (BKN) places two hands to Williams' (LAC) body and grabs and pulls his jersey during the inbound.
Gallinari (LAC) takes more than 5 seconds to inbound the ball and the violation precedes his attempt to call a timeout.
Gallinari (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position on Russell (BKN) at the end of the drive.
Carroll (BKN) splits his feet.
Harrell (LAC) makes contact to Carroll's (BKN) arm during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (LAC) makes slight contact with Harris (BKN) during the drive but the contact does not affect his ability to defend.
Beverley (LAC) makes marginal contact to Allen's (BKN) lower body following the made dunk.
Dinwiddie (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by Williams (LAC).
